eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.manager.ingested

Class MetricDataIngestor

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.manager.ingested.MetricDataIngestor

  • public class MetricDataIngestor
extends Object
    Ingests metric data from a CSV file or a DBMS table and extracts values from a specific attribute. Multi-dimensional point representations are returned, associated with their original object identifiers. Resulting points can be used for generating reference (pivot) points and indexing in multi-distance RR*-tree.

      • getDataType

        public DataType.Type getDataType(String inputFile,
                                 int colValue,
                                 String columnSeparator,
                                 boolean header)
        Examines indicative value of an attribute in a CSV file in order to determine its data type.
        Parameters:
        inputFile - Path to the input CSV file or its URL at a remote server containing the attribute data.
        colValue - An integer representing the ordinal number of the attribute containing the values of the entities.
        columnSeparator - The separator character used between attribute values in the CSV file.
        header - Boolean indicating whether the first line contains attribute names.
        Returns:
        The data type of the specified attribute.

      • importFromCsvFile

        public TreeMap<String,Point> importFromCsvFile(String inputFile,
                                               int colKey,
                                               Integer[] colValues,
                                               String columnSeparator,
                                               String tokenDelimiter,
                                               int maxLines,
                                               boolean header,
                                               Logger log)
        Creates a dictionary of (key,point) pairs of all items read from a CSV file. Concerns properties with values coming from a single or multiple attributes (e.g., locations from lon, lat values held is separate values).
        Parameters:
        inputFile - Path to the input CSV file or its URL at a remote server containing the attribute data.
        maxLines - Instructs reader to only consume the first lines up to this limit.
        colKey - An integer representing the ordinal number of the attribute containing the key of the entities.
        colValues - An array of integers representing the ordinal numbers of the attributes containing the values of the entities.
        columnSeparator - The separator character used between attribute values in the CSV file.
        tokenDelimiter - Delimiter character between tokens in an attribute value.
        header - Boolean indicating whether the first line contains attribute names.
        log - Handle to the logger for statistics and issues over the input data.
        Returns:
        A hash map of (key,point) values.
